Detailed Description

underlying implementation of DataBlockReader.

container for data passed to a module - allows data to extracted sequentially like a input stream.

outputs to standard output the contents of the data block.

Data is output in space seperated decimal byte values. A '>' character indicates the position of the cursor.

Integer sbwDataBlockReader::readInteger (  SBWOSSocket *    sock )  [static]
 

reads an integer in SBW format from sock.

Blocks until an integer value has been sent to the socket. Assumes that the type prefix for the integer either is not present or has already been consumed.

Parameters:
sock  the socket from which to read the integer value.
Returns:
the next integer value read from sock.
